sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: CIDAR MoClo Extension Kit Volume I (Murray Lab)
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: CIDAR MoClo Extension Kit Volume I (Murray Lab)
sbol:Collection.dc:creator: Jet

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: PSal-M
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Promoter regulated by the engineered quorum-sensing activator NahR-M (C75m). Engineered for low leak, high fold-activation, and low cross-talk with other members of the Marionette system. Produces a small amount of transcription constitutively, and is strongly activated by C75m when C75m is complexed with salicylate. Additionally, C75m acts as a repressor of P60m when not complexed with salicylate. Activates »500x compared to repressed state. Has identical sequence to PSalTCC

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: J23150
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Medium-strong constitutive promoter (620x J23112, 0.25x J23119). Part of the Anderson promoter library

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: sfCFPpdt3
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: This is the sfCFP fluorescent protein (see C91m) with the pdt3 mf-Lon degradation tag. This allows sfCFP to be degraded by mf-Lon protease (see C80m) orthogonally to E. coli’s native ClpXP degradation system.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: Gp2 toxin
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: The T7 phage-encoded small protein Gp2 is a non-DNA-binding transcription factor that interacts with the jaw domain of the E coli RNA polymerase B’ subunit and inhibits transcriptionally proficient promoter-complex (RPo) formation. This kills the cell.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: PTac
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Promoter regulated by the engineered repressor LacI (C1d or C63m) or its engineered variant LacI-M (C72m). Has low cross-talk when used with other members of the Marionette system when used with C72m. Constitutively active, and is repressed »500x by C1d, C63m, or C72m when the repressor is not complexed with Isopropyl-B-D-thiogalactiside (IPTG).

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BCD16
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Medium-low strength (»0.1-0.3x BCD2) insulated bi-cistronic RBS from the BCD collection.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: S. pyogenes tracrRNA terminator
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Wild terminator from the S. pyogenes tracrRNA. Required for proper function of guide RNAs with S. pyogenes Cas9 (C41m, C113m and C114m).

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: lambda-cI
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Repressor of the Cro promoter (P9m or P35m) of bacteriophage Lambda (GenBank:J02459.1).

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: SigmaX (ECF20_992)
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: A sigma factor is a bacterial transcription initiation factor that enables specific binding of RNA polymerase (RNAP) to gene promoters. SigmaX plays key roles in coordinating gene transcription during various stress responses.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: L3S2P11
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Synthetic terminator from the Voigt terminator collection. Based on the terminator from the secC-leuU transcriptional unit from E. coli (ECK120034435), with features substituted from other strong natural terminators.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: PLbda-CasRQi
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Constitutive Lambda phage promoter (see P9m) with a downstream attachment site for S. pyogenes dCas9 repression with the gQi guide RNA (see UCT1). Provides constitutive expression, though considerably weaker than the same promoter without a dCas binding site (P9m). Repressed by both the Lambda cI repressor (C24m, or C64m for a temperature-sensitive version) and by dCas when expressed with the gQi guide RNA.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BCD6
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: High strength (0.4-0.9x BCD2) insulated bi-cistronic RBS from the BCD collection.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: J23151
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Strong constitutive promoter (1,245x J23112, 0.49x J23119). Part of the Anderson promoter library

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: MG-apt-C21m
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Identical to U19m, but as a CDS part.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: ccdA antitoxin
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: The peptide antitoxin that bind ccdB (C39m) and neutralizes its toxicity. Originally found on the E. coli F plasmid in the ccd operon with ccdB.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: PLas-M
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Promoter regulated by the engineered quorum-sensing activator LasR-LSTPLVMI (C73m). Engineered for low leak, high fold-activation, and low cross-talk with other members of the Marionette system. Constitutively off, and activated by C73m when C73m is complexed with 3OC12-HSL.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: treRT-LAA
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: This is the treRT repressor, which represses the PTAN promoter, with an LAA degradation tag. treRT is a synthetic repressor created in [1]. treRT was designed as part of a family of transcriptional repressors which have identical repression kinetics but orthogonal targets – for example, treRT represses the PTAN promoter while its cousin treRL represses the PLac promoter with identical kinetics and minimal crosstalk. treRT repression is relieved by the addition of trehalose.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: mScarlet-I-pdt3
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: This is the mScarlet-I fluorescent protein (see part C99m) with the pdt3 mf-Lon degradation tag attached. This allows mScarlet-I to be degraded by mf-Lon protease (see part C80m) orthogonally to E. coli’s native ClpXP degradation system. This mScarlet-I has been codon-optimized for E. coli.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: mScarlet
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: mScarlet red fluorescent protein. Improved RFP molecule that is shifted into higher excitation / emission spectra (see below).

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: PTra*
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Inducible promoter activated by TraR(W) (C62m) bound to 3OC8 AHL.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: ECK120033737
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Natural terminator from the Voigt terminator collection. Pulled from the thrLABC transcriptional unit of E. coli.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: sfYFP-AAV-ssrA
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: This is a sfYFP fluorescent protein (see C51m) with the AAV ssrA degradation tag. This allows sfYFP to be degraded by E. coli’s native ClpX/ClpXP degradation system.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BCD13
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Medium-high strength (»0.5-0.9x BCD2) insulated bi-cistronic RBS from the BCD collection.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: PlacO
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Transcriptional promoter containing two lacO sequences. Similar to P30m but with two lac operators instead of one.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: RiboJ + UTR1
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: The UTR1 RBS (U4m) downstream of a RiboJ self-cleaving RNA sequence. UTR1 provides strong translation, while the RiboJ sequence insulates expression from the gene’s promoter context.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: 50 bp Blank
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: 50 random bases with 50% GC content

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BCD22
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Very low strength (0.02-0.1x BCD2) insulated bi-cistronic RBS from the BCD collection.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: UTR1
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Very strong RBS derived from the T7 gene 10 leader RNA. Provides extremely strong translation.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: mScarlet-I codon optimized
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: The mScarlet-I fluorescent protein was derived from mScarlet (sC59m) with a single amino acid substitution T74I. This version of mScarlet folds much faster than the parent sequence (36 minute maturation half-time vs 174 minute maturation half-time), but is about 30% dimmer. This part has been codon-optimized from the original sequence for expression in E.coli.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: gV1 Cas9 gRNA
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Complete guide RNA (gRNA) for S. pyogenes Cas9. Targeting sequence is taken from [1], below, who use it in conjunction with dCas9 (C41m or C114m) to repress a synthetic promoter containing the target sequence.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: sfYFP
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Fast-folding yellow-fluorescent protein.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: PCinLacO-m
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: PCinLacO is a promoter sequence that allows for combinatorial control over expression by CinR, which is activated by 3OHC14-ASL (positive regulation, C32m), and LacI, which is derepressed by IPTG (negative regulation, C1d or C63m). Effectively encodes the logic “CinR (and Cin AHL) and not LacI”, or, with both regulators present, “Cin AHL and IPTG”.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: sfYFP-DAS-ssrA
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: This is the sfYFP fluorescent protein (see part C51m) with a DAS ssrA degradation tag. This allows sfYFP to be degraded by E. coli’s native ClpXP degradation system.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: Cas9
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: S. pyogenes Cas9 programmable endonuclease. Cas9 makes double-stranded, blunt-end cuts to DNA at almost-arbitrarily programmable locations. The enzyme is targeted using a guide RNA (gRNA), which contains a constant scaffold sequence recognized by the enzyme, and a variable »20bp region specifying the DNA target. Binding (and cutting) also requires that a short protospacer-adjacent motif (PAM) (“NGG”, for S. pyogenes Cas9) be adjacent to the target sequence.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: LasR-LSTPLVMI
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Engineered quorum-sensing activator of PLas-M (P58m). Engineered for low leak, high fold-activation, and low cross-talk with other elements of the Marionette system. Activates P58m when complexed with 3OC12-HSL.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: P13
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Weak strength constitutive promoter.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: Rpa Synthase (RpaI)
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: RpaI synthesizes the quorum-sensing autoinducer molecule 4-coumaroylhomoserine lactone (p-coumaroyl-HSL). The Rpa-AHL molecule is membrane diffusible and bind to RpaR transcriptional regulator to regulate expression via pRpa promoter. Signaling molecules produced by Rpa-I, allows for quorum communication of bacterial systems.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: NahR-M
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Engineered quorum-sensing activator of PSal-M (P60m). Engineered for low leak, high fold-activation, and low cross-talk with other elements of the Marionette system. When not complexed with sodium salicylate, acts as a weak repressor of P60m. Strongly activates P60m when complexed with salicylate. Activates P60m »500x compared to repressed state.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: PLasTetO
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: PLasTetO is a promoter sequence that allows for combinatorial control overexpression by LasR, which is activated by 3OC12-HSL (positive regulation, C73m) and TetR, which is derepressed by anhydrotetracycline (negative regulation, C2d or C27m). Effectively encodes the logic “LasR (and Las AHL) and not TetR” or, with both regulators present, “Las AHL and aTc”.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: gQi Cas9 gRNA
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Complete guide RNA (gRNA) for S. pyogenes Cas9. Targeting sequence is taken from [1], where it is used to repress transcription of mRFP when expressed in conjunction with dCas9 (C41m or C114m). Represses P35m (a strong promoter with a gQi binding site).

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: sfCFP-LAA)
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: This is the sfCFP fluorescent protein (see part C91m) with the LAA ssrA degradation tag. This allows sfCFP to be degraded by E. coli’s native ClpXP degradation system.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: ECK120029600
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Natural terminator from the Voigt terminator collection. Pulled from the spy transcriptional unit of E. coli.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: J23101
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Strong constitutive promoter (1,791x J23112, 0.7x J23119). Part of the Anderson promoter library

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: PCinTetO
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: PCinTetO is a promoter sequence that allows for combinatorial control overexpression by CinR, which is activated by 3OHC14-ASL (positive regulation, C32m), and TetR, which is derepressed by anhydrotetracycline (negative regulation, C2d or C27m). Effectively encodes the logic “CinR (and Cin AHL) and not TetR” or, with both regulators present, “Cin AHL and aTc”.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: mfLon-pdt3 tag
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: This is the mfLon protease (see C80m) with the pdt3 mf-Lon degradation tag attached. This allows mf-Lon to be degraded by mf-Lon protease (C80m) orthogonally to E. coli’s native ClpXP degradation system. This means that the mf-Lon expressed off this sequence will degrade itself.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: PLux76B
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Promoter regulated by the engineered quorum-sensing activator LuxRQFMY (C74m). Engineered for low leak, high fold-activation, and low cross-talk with other members of the Marionette system. Constitutively off, and activated »500x by C74m when C74m is complexed with 3OC6-HSL. This promoter is an intermediate variant, not the final promoter used in the Marionette cell lines.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: P11
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Medium strength constitutive promoter.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: Bxb1 integrase - mScarlet-i-LAA
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Bxb1 integrase/mScarlet-I (C31m/C9m) fusion protein with an LAA ssrA degradation tag. This allows the protein to be degraded by E. coli’s native ClpXP degradation system. Unlike C99m and its derivatives, this mScarlet-I has not been codon-optimized for expression in E. coli.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: L3S1P13
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Synthetic terminator from the Voigt terminator collection. Based on the terminator from the PheA transcriptional unit from E. coli, with features substituted from other strong natural terminators

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: ccdB toxin
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: The ccdB DNA gyrase toxin. Poisons DNA gyrase and causes double strand DNA breakage instead of normal DNA uncoiling. Toxicity of ccdB is abrogated by the gyrA462 (genomic) mutation or concurrent presence of ccdA antitoxin (C79m). Originally found on the E. coli F plasmid in the ccd operon alongside ccdA.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: L3S2P55
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Synthetic terminator from the Voigt terminator collection. Based on the terminator from the secC-leuU transcriptional unit from E. coli (ECK120034435), with features substituted from other strong natural terminators.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: PL-lacO1
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: LacI repressible promoter. Includes σ70 Lac01 promoter and Lac operator. Similar to P32m, but with one Lac operator instead of two.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: modified L3S2P21
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Synthetic terminator based on L3S2P21 from the Voigt terminator collection, mutated to remove restriction sites. Based on the terminator from the secC-leuU transcriptional unit from E. coli (ECK120034435), with features substituted from other strong natural terminators.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: TraR(W)
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: TraR(W) transcriptional activator from [1]. TraR(W) activates transcription from PTra* (P38m) in the presence of 3OC8 AHL. Contains a synonymous mutation (A -> G) at position 511 of the part plasmid sequence (position 507 of the coding sequence) to remove a BbsI restriction site.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: sfCFP
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: This is an sfCFP fluorescent protein that displays improved stability and strong cyan fluorescence compared to CFP.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: RiboJ + BCD2
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: The BCD2 RBS (see U4d, Bicistronic Designs) downstream of a RiboJ selfcleaving RNA sequence. BCD2 provides strong translation, while the RiboJ sequence insulates expression from the gene’s promoter context.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: gN2 gRNA
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Complete guide RNA (gRNA) for S. pyogenes Cas9. Targeting sequence was designed in NUPACK (http://www.nupack.org/) for minimum disruption of the gRNA scaffold sequence.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: NahR-sfGFP fusion
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: The engineered quorum sensing NahR-M protein (C75m) fused to the superfolder green fluorescent protein (C3m) with a 5xGS linker.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: Sigma38 (RpoS)
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Sigma38 is a central regulator of the general stress response in E. coli. It triggers entrance to stationary phase and and many of the physiological changes that occur during that transition.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: TetR
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Tet operator repressor. Binds to the TetO operator (see P12m, P15m) as a tetramer, blocking transcription from the associated promoter. Repression is lifted by binding to tetracycline or its derivative anhydrotetracycline (aTc). Contains no degradation tags (unlike C2d).

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: ChlorR
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: A CDS that confers resistance to chloramphenicol antibiotic. Encodes chloramphenicol acetyltransferase, which enzymatically inactivates chloramphenicol.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: CinR
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: CinR is the transcription factor of the Cin quorum sensing system from Rhizobium legunimosarum. Its canonical cognate AHL is 3OHC14-HSL. When bound to this AHL, CinR activates the PCin promoter (P57m).

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: modified L3S3P11
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Synthetic terminator based on L3S3P11 from the Voigt terminator collection, mutated to remove restriction sites. Based on the terminator from the metZWV transcriptional unit from E. coli (ECK125109870), with features substituted from other strong natural terminators.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: RpaR-TYQEVV
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Engineered quorum-sensing activator of PRpa-M (P66m). Engineered for low leak, high fold-activation, and low cross-talk with other elements of the Marionette system. Activates P66m when complexed with p-coumaroyl-homoserine lactone.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BCD20
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Medium strength (»0.2-0.5x BCD2) insulated bi-cistronic RBS from the BCD collection.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: Weak T7
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: The T7 promoter sequence is responsible for recruiting the T7 bacteriophage RNA polymerase (RNAP). The T7 RNAP recognizes the T7 promoter with extreme specificity. This variant is missing one G at the 3’ end and is significantly weaker than the wild-type promoter.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: T500_noGap, short attachment (T11)
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Engineered transcriptional terminator from the bacteriophage 83 terminator. Carries an extremely strong hairpin braced by the RNA tetraloop GAAA.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: deGFP
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Mutant of eGFP, modified for efficient translation in E. coli cell free extract (TX-TL). Commonly used for characterization of TX-TL extract.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: sfYFP-ssrA
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: This is an sfYFP fluorescent protein (see C51m) with the LAA ssrA degradation tag. This allows sfYFP to be degraded by E. coli’s native ClpX/ClpXP protease system.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: dCas9, BbsI-safe
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: S. pyogenes Cas9 with inactivating mutations in both cutting domains (HNH and RuvC). Binds to double-stranded DNA as guided by a guide RNA sequence, much like wild-type Cas9 (see C113m), but has no nuclease activity. In conjunction with an appropriate guide RNA, dCas9 can be used to repress transcription, or to sterically block binding of other proteins to the target site. Almost identical to C41m, with three synonymous mutations to remove BbsI cut sites.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BCD24
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Low strength (0.08-0.2x BCD2) insulated bi-cistronic RBS from the BCD collection.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: φX174 Lysis Protein (X174E)
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Lysis protein from bacteriophage φX174 (protein E).

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BCD11
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Medium-high strength (»0.5-0.75x BCD2) insulated bi-cistronic RBS from the BCD collection.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: sfGFP
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Super-folder green fluorescent protein. Relative to GFP, has increased thermal stability and better retains its fluorescence when fused to poorly folding proteins.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: Sigma28
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: A sigma factor is a bacterial transcription initiation factor that enables specific binding of RNA polymerase (RNAP) to gene promoters. The protein encoded by this specific sigma factor, sigma28, has been found to be necessary for flagellum formation. The one in the library is a non-endogenous sigma factor protein.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: ECK120033736, modified
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Modified natural terminator from the Voigt terminator collection. Pulled from the hisLGDCBHAF transcriptional unit of E. coli and extended 2bp on the 5’ end and 8bp on the 3’ end.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: KanR
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: A CDS that confers resistance to kanamycin antibiotic. Encodes neomycin phosphotransferase II that enzymatically inactivates kanamycin and other related antibiotics (various aminoglycoside antibiotics, including G418).

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: AiiA degradase
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: AiiA is an AHL lactonase that degrades quorum sensing signaling molecules by opening the lactone ring. It acts on AHL molecules regardless of acyl chain length.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: CinR-CIDDHYRTC n-2v
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Engineered quorum-sensing activator of PCin (P57m). Engineered for low leak, high fold-activation, and low cross-talk with other elements of the Marionette system. Activates P57m »500x when is complexed with 3OHC14-HSL. Note: The Marionette strains contain a similar, but not identical, variant of CinR. To use exactly this part, you will need to supply it in your own construct.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: mfLon protease
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: This is the coding sequence for the mf-Lon protease, the Lon protease described in [1, 2]. The protease degrades ssrA-style tags (see [2]) which are orthogonal to the degradation from E. coli’s native ClpXP degradation machinery. In other words, ClpXP does not degrade proteins with mf-Lon ssrAs and mf-Lon does not degrade proteins with ClpXP ssrAs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: LacI
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: The LacI protein, aka the Lac repressor, binds the lacO DNA sequence as a tetramer, inhibiting transcription. Upon binding allolactose (or its analog isopropyl -B- D-1-thiogalactopyranoside, IPTG), the LacI is released from the lacO sequence, allowing for transcription to proceed. The LacI protein forms a homotetramer, comprised of two homodimeric DNA binding subunits. Therefore, the homotetrameter can function to inhibit transcription by binding at two lacO regions and looping the DNA.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: temperature sensitive lambda repressor (cI857)
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Temperature-sensitive variant of the repressor of the Cro promoter (P9m) of bacteriophage Lambda (GenBank:J02459.1). P9m is a strong promoter that is repressed by C64m at 29°C (and even more strongly at room temperature). At 37°C, C64m unbinds from its target and ceases to repress.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: bxb1 integrase
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: This is the serine integrase from the Mycobacterium Bxb phage. Serine integrases can be used to insert, excise, flip, and swap DNA sequences flanked appropriately by the proper attachment sites – for a review of bxb1 functionality, see [1]. Bxb1 catalyzes recombination between »50 nt sequences known as attB and attP. In nature, attP is found in the phage genome and attB in the bacterial genome. Once recombined, these sequences are converted into attL and attR, which can’t be recombined in the reverse direction.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: MG-apt
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: RNA aptamer for malachite green (MG). Increases the fluorescence of MG several thousand-fold when bound, making MG a fluorophore specific to the aptamer-tagged RNA.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: RhlR
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Rhl quorum sensing receptor. When complexed with its AHL, RhlR activates the PRhl promoter

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: Citrine
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Green/yellow fluorescent protein

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: PRpa-M
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Promoter regulated by the quorum-sensing activator RpaR-TYQEVV (C70m). Engineered for low leak, high fold-activation, and low cross-talk with other members of the Marionette system. Constitutively off, and activated by C70m when C70m is complexed with p-coumaroyl-homoserine lactone.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: PCin
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Promoter regulated by the quorum-sensing activator CinR (C32m) and its engineered variant CinR-M (C71m). Has low cross-talk with other members of the Marionette system. Constitutively off, and activated »500x by CinR when CinR is complexed with 3OHC14-HSL. Note: The CinR variant used in the Marionette System is similar to but not identical to part C71m.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: mScarlet-I-LAA
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: This is the mScarlet-I fluorescent protein (see part C99m) with the LAA ssrA degradation tag. This allows mScarlet-I to be degraded by E. coli’s native ClpXP degradation system. This mScarlet-I has been codon-optimized for expression in E. coli.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: RpaR
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: RpaR transcriptional activator from [1]. RpaR activates transcription from PRpa, which is not included in this kit, in the presence of p-coumaroyl HSL. It may also activate PRpa-M (P37m), though we have not tested that functionality

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: LuxRQ FMY
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Engineered quorum-sensing activator of PLux76B (P59m). Engineered for low leak, high fold-activation, and low cross-talk with other elements of the Marionette system. Activates P59m »500x when complexed with 3OC6-HSL. This protein is an intermediate variant from [1], not the final promoter used in the Marionette cell lines.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: Bujard RBS
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: A strong RBS from the gramicidin synthase gene of E. coli KLY. Roughly comparable to U4m in strength.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: RhlI
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: RhlI is the signal synthase from the Rhl quorum sensing system. Synthesizes N-butyryl-L-homoserine lactone (the Rhl AHL) from S-adenosylmethionine and an appropriately-charged coenzyme A, both of which are typically plentiful in the cell.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: T7 RNA polymerase
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: RNA polymerase from the T7 bacteriophage. The T7 RNAP recognizes the T7 promoter with extreme specificity. Use to activate transcription from P18m.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: Pr-OR1-OR2
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Promoter for the Cro repressor protein in bacteriophage Lambda (GenBank:J02459.1), with a single-base modification. Provides very strong constitutive expression,and is repressed by the lambda cI repressor.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: pir protein
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: The pir protein is required for R6K plasmid replication.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: mRFP
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Monomeric red fluorescent protein. Somewhat fast-maturing mutant of DsRed-Express.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: Cerulean
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Cyan fluorescent protein

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: LacI-M
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Engineered quorum-sensing activator of PTac (P61m). Engineered for low leak, high fold-activation, and low cross-talk with other elements of the Marionette system. Represses P61m »500x unless complexed with Isopropyl-B-D-thiogalactiside (IPTG).

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: AmpR
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: A CDS that confers resistance to ampicillin antibiotic. Encodes betalactamase, which enzymatically inactivates ampicillin and most other beta-lactam antibiotics (most other -cillin antibiotics, including penicillin and carbenicillin). May also inactivate some cephalosporin antibiotics. This is the bla-TEM variant, likely from a transposon integrated into an E.coli strain.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: deCFP
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Cyan fluorescent protein modified for efficient translation in E. coli cell free extract (TX-TL). Sometimes used for characterization of TX-TL extract.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: TP901 integrase
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: This is the serine integrase from the TP901 phage. Serine integrases can be used to insert, excise, flip, and swap DNA sequences flanked appropriately by the proper attachment sites.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: sfYFP-pdt3
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: This is the sfYFP fluorescent protein (see C51m) with the pdt3 mf-Lon degradation tag. This allows sfYFP to be degraded by mf-Lon protease (see C80m) orthogonally to E. coli’s native ClpXP degradation system.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: dCas9
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: S. pyogenes Cas9 with inactivating mutations in both cutting domains (HNH and RuvC). Binds to double-stranded DNA as guided by a guide RNA sequence, much like wild-type Cas9 (see C113m), but has no nuclease activity. In conjunction with an appropriate guide RNA, dCas9 can be used to repress transcription, or to sterically block binding of other proteins to the target site.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BCD14
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Medium-high strength (»0.2-0.7x BCD2) insulated bi-cistronic RBS from the BCD collection

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: Prpa
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Inducible quorum-sensing promoter promoter activated by RpaR (C61m) bound to p-coumaroyl homoserine lactone signaling molecule.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: mSpinach
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: An RNA aptamer that fluoresces green when complexed with DFHBI, DFHBI-1T, or other structural analogues. Useful in bulk measurements as a readout of transcription or degradation, or in microscopy for those purposes or to visualize localization.
